<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-11-25T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-11-25T16:00:00-05:00" n="223" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d223">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">821.51/1748: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Chargé in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-11-25T16:00:00-05:00">November 25, 1933—4
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>79. Your 96, November 23, 10 p.m. Endeavor to see Olaya at once and
                            ascertain if there is any possibility of his vetoing Article 2 of the
                            Debt Bill, and also, any possibility of his vetoing the Budget Bill in
                            view of failure to include any appropriation for funded debt
                            services.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>